sql:
SELECT COUNT(media_id) AS total_media_files, 
       MAX(file_size) AS largest_file_size 
FROM media_files;

external_knowledge:
- "items" refers to media files;
- "kind of file" corresponds to file types such as video or audio;
- "media collection" indicates the database table from which the data is being retrieved.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(media_id) AS total_media_files, file_type
FROM media_files
GROUP BY file_type;

SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_downloads, COUNT(DISTINCT user_id) AS unique_users
FROM media_downloads
WHERE download_type = 'download';

SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_downloads
FROM media_downloads
WHERE media_id = 1;

SELECT file_name, clicks AS total_clicks
FROM media_files
ORDER BY total_clicks DESC;

SELECT COUNT(media_id) AS file_count, SUM(clicks) AS total_clicks
FROM media_files
WHERE category_id = 1;

SELECT SUM(clicks) AS total_clicks
FROM media_files
WHERE user_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- "golden seeds" refers to video files;
- "perfect clarity" refers to the quality level 'HD 720p';
- "sown" is a metaphorical term for the action of adding files to the database;
- "the garden" is a metaphor for the database or media collection;
- "the year of the great harvest" is a metaphorical expression for the year 2023.

sql:
SELECT mf.file_name, q.quality_name
FROM media_files mf
INNER JOIN qualities q ON mf.quality_id = q.quality_id;
